<HEADLINE>
KITNA RALLIES SEAHAWKS PAST DALLAS IN PRESEASON OPENER 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By CLARE FARNSWORTH  
 c.1998 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ The Seahawks' present didn't look all that sharp
in Friday night's preseason opener. But a big part of their past
and several pieces of their future did.
</P>
<P>
   After the No. 1 offense struggled in its brief appearance,
backup quarterback Jon Kitna came on to lead the Seahawks to a
touchdown and two field goals and rookie running back Ahman Green
scored the other TD as Seattle outlasted the Dallas Cowboys 20-19
on a hot, muggy evening at Texas Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   The efforts of Kitna and Green were needed to offset a two-TD
performance by Chris Warren, the Seahawks' all-time leading rusher
who signed with the Cowboys after being released by Seattle in
March.
</P>
<P>
   Among the 59,357 in attendance was Warren Moon, the Seahawks
starting quarterback who is holding out. Moon, who traveled to the
game from his offseason home in Houston, talked to teammates and
coach Dennis Erickson after the game, and later said that despite
his appearance nothing has changed in the impasse between him and
the club to renegotiate his contract.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was a typical preseason opener,'' said Erickson, who has
won three of four as Seahawks coach. ``There were some good things
for both teams.''
</P>
<P>
   Kitna, who will start next Saturday's prese$s;J918006350017 ;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-02-98 1207EDT &QL; 
