   SEC-QBS _ There will be several new faces lining up at
quarterback in the SEC this season. Tee Martin takes over for
Peyton Manning at Tennessee, Ben Leard steps in for Dameyune Craig
at Auburn and the QB situation at Georgia is still undecided after
the graduation of Mike Bobo. The only established returning starter
at QB in the conference is Kentucky's Tim Couch, who will enter the
season as the Heisman Trophy favorite. A look at the quarterbacks
in the SEC heading into the '98 season. (Barnhart, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
