<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-02 20:03 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A4402 &Cx1f; ttc-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-LADN-BUDGET &LR;      08-02 0197
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Monday, Aug. 3 and thereafter. For questions about stories, contact
William Toren at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   SEX-CENTER (Los Angeles) -- Suburban Northridge is not the first
place people tend to think of as a hotbed of sex research, but the
Cal State University campus there has been quietly building an
international reputation among academics. Now, new director James
Elias is thrusting the center into the limelight by including cross
dressers, prostitutes, and porn stars in its upcoming global
conference. By Sharline Chiang. (Will move in the ``a'' national
and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   BOX-OFFICE (Los Angeles) -- The much-praised ``Saving Private
Ryan''scored another box office victory, taking in an estimated
$23.3 million in its second weekend to lead the pack for DreamWorks
SKG. Disney's remake of ``The Parent Trap'' opened in second place,
with an estimated $11.5 million. By Dave McNary. (Will move in the
``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
