<HEADLINE>
IF LASORDA IS RIGHT, WATCH OUT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Trader Tommy will be insufferable if the Dodgers
make the playoffs in a couple of months.
</P>
<P>
   No one believed me, he'll bellow. I told you so.
</P>
<P>
   So you did.
</P>
<P>
   By exporting from San Antonio and Albuquerque to import
big-league experience _ something Fearful Freddy Claire cringed at
_ Lasorda has actually brought some sanity to an insane season.
</P>
<P>
   It was Vin Scully, of all people, wondering out loud on the
Dodgers TV broadcast the other night whether Lasorda is really a
general manager thinking like a manager as he continues to bail
water from the sinking season.
</P>
<P>
   Of course he is. Buy now, pay later. It's the American way.
Besides, there's a good chance Lasorda won't be around to take the
heat if these deals don't work out.
</P>
<P>
   There was a definite lack of flair in Claire, who recently set
up a new office in Pasadena and is waiting by the phone to see if
anyone needs a new GM.
</P>
<P>
   Just as there's a definite sorta order brought by Lasorda....
</P>
<P>
   Lasorda insists he's the interim GM and he wants to bring
someone else in who ``is young and knowledgeable and I can work
with.'' And deflect blame if something goes wrong....
</P>
<P>
   Marty Noble, the senior writer on the Mets' beat for New York's
Newsday, has been telling colleagues: ``I have seven words. If I
can verify Bobby Valentine said them, I can get Bobby Valentine
fired.'' Would those words be: ``Please, Tommy, get me to L.A.
Hurry.''...
</P>
<P>
   You say Grudzielanek, I see Grabarkewitz....
</P>
<P>
   You say Carlos Perez, I see Pascual Perez....
</P>
<P>
   The Dodgers remain one of two teams that haven't won four in a
row this year....
</P>
<P>
   Matt Franco, the Mets infielder from Westlake High who ruined
the Dodgers' night Saturday with a pinch-hit, ninth-inning home
run, is the nephew of actor Kurt Russell....
</P>
<P>
   Wilton Guerrero just found out from his brother, Vladimir, that
the price of cork is higher in Canada....
</P>
<P>
   For old times' sake, let the highlight of Saturday's ``Hollywood
Stars Night'' be Charlton Heston blazing through the Dodger Stadium
field-level seats on a motorcycle, just like he did in ``The Omega
Man.''...
</P>
<P>
   After the way the Angels fumbled the opportunity to pick up Mark
McGwire at the trading deadline last year, what's so surprising
about the fact the AL West leaders did nothing this time while
Texas changed the entire complexion of its team?...
</P>
<P>
   The NBA labor talks are... sorry, I had to yawn there... are
supposed to resume Thursday, two months before the camps open....
</P>
<P>
   Maybe it's laying the groundwork for the ``Home Team, Fox
Attitude'' gang doing some Lancaster JetHawks games down the road.
Maybe it's not. But Fox Sports West 2's experiment tonight by
airing a Triple-A contest between Las Vegas and Albuquerque at 6
could open the door to more televised minor-league baseball....
</P>
<P>
   Take Sept. 9 in Cincinnati off Dennis Reyes in the Mark McGwire
home run pool....
</P>
<P>
   Howie Long's next movie: ``A Dollar For the Dead,'' made for
TNT. It's a Western with Emilio Estevez and William Forsythe coming
out in October....
</P>
<P>
   Brian Robbins and Mike Tollin, the executive producers of the
HBO drama series ``Arli$$,'' are wrapping up a movie called
``Varsity Blues,'' due out in the fall. Jon Voight plays an
overbearing high school football coach who thrusts backup QB James
Van Der Beek (Dawson from ``Dawson's Creek'') into the
spotlight....
</P>
<P>
   Justin Fargas alert: One-on-One Sports, with its AM-1540
affiliate in L.A., signed to do University of Michigan football
games this season....
</P>
<P>
   L.A. investment groups are being assembled !ital!as we speak in
an attempt to make an offer to buy the San Francisco 49ers, which
could be soon sold by Eddie DeBartolo because of his legal
troubles, reports the San Francisco Chronicle....
</P>
<P>
   So what !ital!is up with Quincy Watts?...
</P>
<P>
   The Raiders have about 5,000 seat license holders who haven't
renewed, which could bring the total who forfeited their PSLs to
12,000....
</P>
<P>
   Lynx Golf, which Fred Couples talked TV celebs like Jim Nantz
and Jim Lampley into investing in last year, has filed for
bankruptcy....
</P>
<P>
   The Tampa Bay Lightning's new offseason ad campaign ends with
the tag: ``No more excuses, it's time to just shut up and play
hockey.''...
</P>
<P>
   Sponsorship update: That Kentucky Derby prep race that used to
be known as the Jim Beam Stakes has been changed to the Gallery
Furniture.com Stakes.... &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
