<HEADLINE>
SUBORDINATION BEATS WESTERN FOES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEVIN MODESTI  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   DEL MAR _ Subordination took advantage of the favorite's
starting-gate injury to dominate Sunday's Eddie Read Handicap,
which became the third major Southern California race in a little
more than a month to be won by a beast from the East.
</P>
<P>
   That trend is notable, because for decades trainers believed
shipping horses from East to West was inherently more difficult
than going from West to East.
</P>
<P>
   Now, it's fair to ask if that was a myth, if that was a crafty
excuse for eastern horses' defeats, or if New York and Kentucky
simply have all the best horses these days.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think it's still a big disadvantage,'' said Gary Sciacca,
the Belmont Park-based trainer of Subordination, who led from gate
to wire under jockey David Flores to win by a length. ``Unless
you've got a great horse.''
</P>
<P>
   Kentucky-based Escena won the Vanity Handicap at Hollywood Park
in June. New York-based Skip Away won the Hollywood Gold Cup in
July. And now New York-based Subordination has won the $300,000
Eddie Read, pushing his earnings over $1 million in one of the
major turf races of the summer.
</P>
<P>
   It's the second successful cross-country trip for the 4-year-old
colt, who won the Hollywood Derby in November. Since then, he won
races on both turf and dirt in Florida and New York.
</P>
<P>
   The Eddie Read became an easier mark when the hyperactive
Labeeb, 8-5 on the tote board, was ordered scratched by the track
veterinarian after thrashing around, hitting his head on the
starting gate and sustaining a friction burn on a hind leg. Labeeb
was reported in good shape back at Neil Drysdale's barn Sunday
evening.
</P>
<P>
   The new favorite was another Drysdale-trained horse, Hawksley
Hill. But the weekend turned out to be a complete bust for
Drysdale, whose Fiji ran third at 2-5 odds in the Ramona Handicap
won by See You Soon on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Hawksley Hill ran last most of the way before rallying late to
take third in a three-way photo between Bonapartiste and Magellan.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, Flores put Subordination on a comfortable lead from
the outside post position and they held it for 1[ miles. Sciacca, a
38-year-old New York native, said he replaced regular rider Eibar
Coa because Flores would be more familiar with the Del Mar turf
course.
</P>
<P>
   With that hometown assist, Subordination became the first
eastern horse to ship in to win the Eddie Read in the 25-year
history of the race.
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Escena and jockey Jerry Bailey were 1-5 in the Go for
Wand Handicap at Saratoga on Sunday but lost a stretch-long duel to
Aldiza and Mike Smith. The top-ranked mare had won four in a row.
She carried 11 pounds more than her upsetter.... Del Mar is
guaranteeing the pick-six pool will be at least $2 million on Aug.
15, the day of the Pacific Classic. It's an amplification of the
gimmick introduced with much success at Hollywood Park, where
guarantees of $1 million and $1.5 million produced pick-six pools
of $3.3 million and $3.8 million.... Touch Gold, who arrived here
Saturday to run in the Pacific Classic, went 1{ miles Sunday in his
first gallop over the track.
</P>
</TEXT>
